5 Section 2. KRS 304.47-020 is amended to read as follows:
6 (1) For the purposes of this subtitle, a person or entity commits a "fraudulent insurance
7 act" if he or she engages in any of the following, including but not limited to
8 matters relating to workers' compensation:
9 (a) Knowingly and with intent to defraud or deceive presents, causes to be
10 presented, or prepares with knowledge or belief that it will be presented to an
11 insurer, Board of Claims, Special Fund, or any agent thereof:
12 1. Any[ written or oral] statement as part of, or in support of, a claim for
13 payment or other benefit pursuant to an insurance policy or from a "self-
14 insurer" as defined by KRS Chapter 342, knowing that the statement
15 contains any false, incomplete, or misleading information concerning
16 any fact or thing material to a claim;[ or]
17 2. To the extent not otherwise included under subparagraph 1. of this
18 paragraph, any statement that misrepresents the scope of damages,
19 including repair costs and other expenses, associated with a property,
20 casualty, or property and casualty insurance claim, including any
21 claim for towing or storage benefits under a property, casualty, or
22 property and casualty insurance policy; or
23 3.[2.] Any statement as part of, or in support of, an application for an
24 insurance policy, for renewal, reinstatement, or replacement of
25 insurance, or in support of an application to a lender for money to pay a
26 premium, knowing that the statement contains any false, incomplete, or
27 misleading information concerning any fact or thing material to the
