16 (c) One million dollars ($1,000,000) or more, in which case it is a Class B felony.
17 (3) A person, with the purpose to establish or maintain a criminal syndicate or to
18 facilitate any of its activities, shall be guilty of engaging in organized crime, a Class
19 B felony, if he or she engages in any of the activities set forth in KRS 506.120(1).
20 (4) A person convicted of a crime established in this section shall be punished by:
